Jennifer,
Don&#39;t worry about feeling weird.  I&#39;ve felt &quot;weird&quot; most of my life... though I can&#39;t speak for anyone here (and this is only my second post here, lol)  I&#39;d venture to say that many other people in this group have experienced similar feelings at one point or another.
I forget the actual website, but I too have read in the last few days the theory that some of what comes through the ghost box can be the thoughts of the living... and that this would make sense given the idea that ghosts are the survival of our consciousness after the death of the physical body.  If ghosts are simply the survival of our consciousness, it would be that same consciousness that exists in us while we are alive, and would therefore operate upon the ghost box by technically the same mechanism... or so goes the theory... upon first ponder, it makes a lot of sense...
As far as being ridiculed, remember what the say about The Truth..

Truth passes through three phases:

First it is ridiculed. 
Second it is fiercely and violently opposed. 
Third, it becomes self-evident. 
 Arthur Schopenhauer



